REST API (FastAPI / Node)
   â†“
Video Processor (FFmpeg)
   â†“
AI Model (Generative Video Model)
   â†“
Storage (S3 / Local)

ğŸ”‘ API Features

Upload video clip

Specify extension duration

Choose quality & frame count

Track processing status

Download extended video

ğŸŒ Base URL
https://api.generative-extend.ai/v1

ğŸ” Authentication
Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>

ğŸ“¥ 1. Create Generative Extend Job
Endpoint
POST /extend
Request (multipart/form-data)
| Field          | Type   | Required | Description                             |
| -------------- | ------ | -------- | --------------------------------------- |
| video          | file   | Yes      | Input video file                        |
| extend_seconds | number | Yes      | Duration to extend (1â€“5 recommended)    |
| fps            | number | No       | Output frame rate (default: source fps) |
| resolution     | string | No       | same / 1080p / 4k                       |
| quality        | string | No       | low / medium / high                     |

Example URL
curl -X POST https://api.generative-extend.ai/v1/extend \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -F "video=@clip.mp4" \
  -F "extend_seconds=2" \
  -F "quality=high"
Response
{
  "job_id": "gx_91f23ab",
  "status": "queued",
  "estimated_time_sec": 45
}

ğŸ“Š 2. Check Job Status
Endpoint
GET /extend/{job_id}/status
Response
{
  "job_id": "gx_91f23ab",
  "status": "processing",
  "progress": 68
}

Status Values

queued

processing

completed

failed

ğŸ“¤ 3. Download Extended Video
Endpoint
GET /extend/{job_id}/download
Response

200 OK â†’ video/mp4

404 â†’ job not ready

410 â†’ expired file

